Class myMap

java.lang.Object
myMap
public class myMap extends Object
The myMap class is used to create and manipulate a LinkedHashMap that stores info objects for each letter in a given string. The LinkedHashMap is created by splitting the given input string into words and storing each letter in the map as a key with an associated info object that contains a count and a list of the words in which the letter appears.

      public myMap​(String input, ArrayList<info> valuesList)
      Constructs a myMap object by creating a LinkedHashMap and populating it with the letters from the given input string. Each letter is stored as a key with an associated info object that contains a count of occurrences and a list of the words in which the letter appears. The LinkedHashMap is populated using an existing ArrayList of info objects.

      valuesList - The ArrayList of info objects used to populate the LinkedHashMap.
